videos.description: Kansas State's Barry Brown gets the steal and the Wildcats go out running for the layup on the other end.
videos.headline: Defense leads to offense for Kansas State

videos.description: D.J Johnson finds Kamau Stokes, who hits the 3-pointer over a Baylor defender.
videos.headline: K-State's Stokes drains 3-pointer over defender

videos.description: Johnathan Motley gets the loose ball and then slams it in.
videos.headline: Baylor's Motley finishes with the dunk

videos.description: Carlbe Ervin finds the cutting  D.J Johnson for the layup.
videos.headline: Nice pass by Baylor's Ervin leads to lay-in

videos.description: Johnathan Motley gets the offensive rebound and finishes with the dunk plus the foul.
videos.headline: Motley slams one for Baylor

videos.description: Manu Lecomte hits the long 3-pointer to cut into Kansas State's lead.
videos.headline: Baylor's Lecomte hits the deep 3-pointer

videos.description: Baylor attempts to tie the game in the final seconds, but D.J. Johnson blocks the attempt to seal a 56-54 victory for Kansas State over the No. 2 Bears.
videos.headline: Kansas State's last-second block seals win over Baylor

videos.description: Wildcats Stokes explains what his team did well in victory over Baylor.
videos.headline: Kansas State's Stokes talks about the differences down the stretch in win over Baylor
